    "See jupyter notebook for an interactive demo.\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Thompson Sampling\n",
    ":::{style=\"font-size: .8em\"}\n",
    "Thompson sampling uses Bayesian statistics to make optimal decisions for the Bayesian bandits that combines exploration with explotation.\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.center-text}\n",
    "<img src=\"images/bayesian_testing/thompson_octopus.png\" width=500/>\n",
    ":::\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "## Thompson Sampling\n",
    ":::{style=\"font-size: .8em\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "1. _**Set up the prior**_: Use a uniform distribution to represent the initial win probability for each machine.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. _**Sample**_: Randomly draw one win‑probability value from the prior distribution for each machine.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. _**Decide**_: Choose the machine whose sampled win probability is the highest.\n",
    "\n",
    "4. _**Play**_: Play the selected machine.\n",
    "\n",
    "5. _**Perform the Bayesian update**_: Update the win‑probability distribution of the selected machine based on the observed outcome.\n",
    "\n",
    "6. _**Sample**_: Draw a new random win‑probability value from the updated distributions.\n",
    "\n",
    "7. _**Repeat**_: Continue with Steps 3–6.\n",
    "\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## 4 Slot Machines\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{style=\"font-size: .8em\"}"
